results.name: Tetrangle where T(n,H(u),H(v)) is the coefficient of e(v) in m(u), where u and v are integer partitions of n, H is Heinz number, m is monomial symmetric functions, and e is elementary symmetric functions.
comment: The Heinz number of an integer partition (y_1, ..., y_k) is prime(y_1) * ... * prime(y_k).
Also the coefficient of h(v) in f(u), where f is forgotten symmetric functions and h is homogeneous symmetric functions.
xref: This is a regrouping of the triangle A321746.
results.author: _Gus Wiseman_, Nov 22 2018
